    <item>
      <title>Execution Environments</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/articles/tech/ansible/archive/execution-environments/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/articles/tech/ansible/archive/execution-environments/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Why use EEs?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portable Ansible environments
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;includes Ansible core version&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All desired collections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Python dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bindep dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anything you need to run a playbook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A container that has a specific version of Ansible. Can test execution in a specific Ansible environment to make sure it will work with that version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
